He still attracts gratitude for the election victory, which was seen - despite subsequent problems for the economy - as the best result for business. He attacked the Tories for building 'a bonfire of pre-election commitments'. The government's efforts to secure a framework for long-term prosperity was beginning to pay off. The past 12 months have been hijacked by internal party differences over Europe, by the debacle surrounding UK withdrawal from the exchange rates mechanism of the European Monetary System, and by a continuing, deep recession which has disappointed and alienated many traditional Tory supporters in business. 